<div id="foogallery-gallery-576" class="foogallery-container foogallery-owl-carousel foogallery-lightbox-foobox-free owl-carousel hover-effect-zoom  ">

				<div class="foo-item" >
			<a  href="https://uicarchives.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/10/2015/01/UA_90_999_0005.31.jpg" data-caption-title="Architecture &amp; Art building spiral capability illustration." data-caption-desc="Walter Netsch&#039;s Field Theory places a square at 45 degrees on another square and clusters those units until the plan is complete.&nbsp;  This drawing for the Architecture &amp; Art building illustrates this double-helix pattern, a play on the recent DNA discoveries at the time.&nbsp; (086 UA 90 999 0005.3)" data-attachment-id="958"><img  src="https://uicarchives.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/10/cache/2015/01/UA_90_999_0005_31/2814848366.jpg" alt="Architecture &amp; Art building-Spiral Capability" width="150" height="150" /></a>			</div> 
				<div class="foo-item" >
			<a  href="https://uicarchives.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/10/2015/01/UA_90_999_0010.jpg" data-caption-title="Architecture and Art building nearing completion, ca. 1969." data-caption-desc="View: east.  (086 UA 90-999 0010)" data-attachment-id="961"><img  src="https://uicarchives.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/10/cache/2015/01/UA_90_999_0010/1092134813.jpg" alt="Campus Construction, aerial, ca. 1969" width="150" height="150" /></a>			</div> 
				<div class="foo-item" >
			<a  href="https://uicarchives.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/10/2015/01/UA_90_999_0005.1.jpg" data-caption-title="Architecture &amp;  Art &ndash; envisioned ground level and first level floor plan." data-caption-desc="Sixty percent of the building was not completed.&nbsp; See the following as-constructed floor plan.&nbsp;
